
[1]righteous

   RIGHTEOUS, a. ri'chus.

   1. Just; accordant to the divine law. Applied to persons, it denotes
   one who is holy in heart, and observant of the divine commands in
   practice; as a righteous man. Applied to things, it denotes consonant
   to the divine will or to justice; as a righteous act. It is used
   chiefly in theology, and applied to God, to his testimonies and to his
   saints.

   The righteous, in Scripture, denote the servants of God, the saints.

   2. Just; equitable; merited.

   And I thy righteous doom will bless.
